: "user experience"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2020-04-07T14:37:49Z", "updated_at": "2020-04-07T14:38:02Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "#### What is the problem?\r\n\r\n- this is an often to use \"switch\", but config variable name is not trivial to remember/type\r\n- there is a `--mode` switch already, switching the mode requires adjusting this config name\r\n\r\ne.g., compare\r\n```\r\ndatalad -c datalad.search.index-egrep-documenttype=all search path:.*T1w.*\r\n```\r\nto\r\n```\r\ndatalad search --type=all path:.*T1w.*\r\n```\r\n?\r\n\r\nSo  I think it would be great to have an easy to find/use option to `search` to specify what to search among.  It would override `index-MODE-documenttype` if specified.\r\n\r\nHow should be named? I feel that `documenttype` is too \"whoosh-inspired\" (`document` generally is an alien term to datalad, and I would not really call \"dataset\" a \"document\") and unnecessarily long.  I do not quite like `--type` since too generic.  Other possible choices: `--what`, `--target`, `--level`, ...?  ", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4381/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4381/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}